 Properties worth millions of naira were on Wednesday destroyed by a windstorm that accompanied a rainfall in Yenagoa, capital of Bayelsa State. On Tuesday, a fierce windstorm had destroyed the broadcast mast of Glory FM, a radio station owned by state government.



